fe to break you. Remember all the good things God has done, and fill your heart with faith\n\n- Latika\n|\nSoon, when all is well, you're going to look back on this period of your life and be so glad that you never gave up.\n\n- Brittany\n|\nYou can’t give what you don’t have. To write, you must read. To write well, read well.\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, How You Can Write Your Dream Book\n|\nIf you have God’s calling, the circumstances around you do not matter; God knows how to remove every obstacle\n\n- Sunday\n|\nIf you tell the truth, you don't have to remember anything.\n\n- Mark\n|\nI read the way a person might swim, to save his or her life. I wrote that way too.\n\n- Mary Oliver, Wild Geese\n|\nIf God exists, I hope he has a good excuse.\n\n- Woody\n|\nWhoever desires to be free, shall search for the Truth.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nHappiness is like a ripple. If you're the origin, you will get happiness back with same frequency.\n\n- saadshah\n|\n...if you do not even understand what words say, how can you expect to pass judgement on what words conceal?\n\n- H.D.\n|\nDo I dare ask him for what I want,As if I knew it,Could find it on some pageIn some chapterIn some book?\n\n- Stasia Ward Kehoe, Audition\n|\nIf you believe in something because of miracles, then another kind of miracles can make you deny it.\n\n- Toba\n|\nDon't blame my heart's appetite for how it chooses to feast, for my heart is a wild lover, an all-consuming beast.\n\n- Melody  Lee, Moon Gypsy\n|\nA clear vision, backed by definite plans, gives you a tremendous feeling of confidence and personal power.\n\n- Brian Tracy, The Gift of Self-Confidence\n|\nHer faith in a loving and forgiving God is strong, but she worships laughter.\n\n- Miriam Toews, Swing Low\n|\nWhen love writes a letter, joy is its ink.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nThe most essential gift for a good writer is a built-in, shock-proof, shit detector. This is the writer's radar and all great writers have had it.\n\n- Ernest\n|\nIf it’s going to be a world with no time for sentiment, it’s not a world that I want to live in.\n\n- Christopher Isherwood, A Single Man\n|\nWe're here to work, not to make friends,\n\n- Tandec2016\n|\nThere's nothing so heavy as books, sir--unless it's bricks.\n\n- Graham Greene, The Ministry of Fear\n|\nA man’s life is not qualified by how much wealth, power, pleasure or control he has, but by the values of godliness he possesses.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nThe precious gems are hidden, it is not easy to find them.\n\n- Kamaran Ihsan Salih, Latest Proverbs\n|\nBooks can be the people we never get to meet, ancestors or far neighbors.\n\n- Elizabeth Knox, The Vintner's Luck\n|\nMaybe it was me,' Grandma said.'Sometimes they sneak out.Did I fart?\n\n- Janet Evanovich, To the Nines\n|\nΔύο υπερβολές : ν' αποκλείουμε το Λόγο, και να μη δεχόμαστε παρά μόνο το Λόγο.\n\n- Blaise Pascal, Pensées\n|\nOne can never 'fall' in love, you must rise to it's level of consciousness. Love is not a feeling, it's a state of MIND!\n\n- T.C.\n|\n...the more I felt that perhaps believing in fairies was more important than seeing them. In seeing, there is often question and doubt.\n\n- Hazel Gaynor, The Cottingley Secret\n|\nFor you to be great, you must learn to convert every second of your life.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nSometimes one likes foolish people for their folly, better than wise people for their wisdom.\n\n- Elizabeth Gaskell, Wives and Daughters\n|\nWhen you win, you often lose, that's just a fact. There's no currency to straighten a warped spirit, or open a closed heart, a selfish heart...\n\n- Abraham Verghese, Cutting for Stone\n|\nI wished to tell the truth, for truth always conveys its own moral to those who are able to receive it.\n\n- Anne Brontë, The Tenant of Wildfell Hall Volume I\n|\nWe outgrow love like other things and put it in a drawer, till it an antique fashion 